    <item>
      <title>Passing Around Skeletons - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2026/06/30/passing-around-skeletons/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2026/06/30/passing-around-skeletons/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 02:34:07 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18669" class="post-18669 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Passing Around Skeletons&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;In mid-June, Mira gave me an interesting gift when she was clearing out some old junk: her skeleton! 🩻 Although I don&amp;#8217;t think it wasn&amp;#8217;t actually &lt;em&gt;her &lt;/em&gt;skeleton; she was still standing upright after all, so that was a &lt;em&gt;dead &lt;/em&gt;giveaway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260619_HNI_0017.jpg" alt="Mira: You wouldn't want my nice skeleton or anything, would you?" class="wp-image-18670" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;If I didn&amp;#8217;t have one, I&amp;#8217;d be jelly!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;And just a few moments later, Boots complimented me on my new skeleton! I guess the word really spread fast! It &lt;em&gt;rattled &lt;/em&gt;through the community at break-neck speeds. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260619_HNI_0020.jpg" alt="Boots: You're the proud owner of the finest skeleton I've ever seen!" class="wp-image-18671" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He offered me 840 bells for it, and I figured I could spare a rib, so I agreed to sell it. Boots was happy to have it, and he was probably relieved that it didn&amp;#8217;t cost an arm and a leg. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Sorry if my skeleton puns were bad&amp;#8230; to the bone. I hope you found at least some of them to be humerus. 🦴 And if not, I have a bone to pick with you. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I later got to see the inside of Marina&amp;#8217;s house now that she has unpacked. But Marina could only see the inside of her eyelids, since she was sleeping at the time.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260619_HNI_0023.jpg" alt="The inside of Marina's house." class="wp-image-18672" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yesterday, it was raining (and storming) in Forest. Inkwell was feeling sad that he was going to be soaked from head to toe&amp;#8230;in ink.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260629_HNI_0024.jpg" alt="Inkwell: Geez... Before long, I'll be soaked from head to toe, in ink." class="wp-image-18673" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;But isn&amp;#8217;t that normal for you?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I was delivering something from Marina to Inkwell, but Inkwell intended it as a gift to me. It was an orange tie-dye tank. He said he wears his while training&amp;#8230;in ink, of course.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260629_HNI_0029.jpg" alt="Inkwell: Pretty cool, huh? Everyone should have an orange tie-dye tank!" class="wp-image-18674" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260629_HNI_0030.jpg" alt="Inkwell: I like to wear mine during training! In ink!" class="wp-image-18675" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Meanwhile, Marina told me that the rain was making her feet soaked and wrinkly. I don&amp;#8217;t need to hear this.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260629_HNI_0031.jpg" alt="Marina: All the walking I've been doing today has my feet all soaked and wrinkly, blurp!" class="wp-image-18676" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Today, I found Hornsby just standing under the illuminated arch. It wasn&amp;#8217;t even turned on yet, but my favorite blue rhino was already charged up by the sight of it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260630_HNI_0037.jpg" alt="Hornsby stands under a non-illuminated illuminated arch." class="wp-image-18677" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;When I spoke with him, he asked me for a new piece of furniture. The only thing I had with me was a mini tootoid that I had just dug up. But he didn&amp;#8217;t mind it at all. In fact, he found it to be deliciously good.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260630_HNI_0039.jpg" alt="Hornsby: Decorating with a gyroid is like adding a friend to my home! So awesome, I ate it." class="wp-image-18678" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He rewarded me with a kiddie chair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Benjamin the dog was camping over at the campsite today. He&amp;#8217;s not my favorite dog, but it didn&amp;#8217;t really matter anyway because my town is full.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260630_HNI_0041.jpg" alt="Benjamin, at the campsite: Hey! Are you from this town?" class="wp-image-18679" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Marina asked me to make another delivery, this time it was some clothing for Mira. But because I guessed incorrectly about what the gift was, I didn&amp;#8217;t get rewarded for the delivery. But at least Marina threw some shade at Mira. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260630_HNI_0050.jpg" alt="Marina: I wasn't really worried, though. Mira doesn't care quite so much about manners." class="wp-image-18680" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;And while at Re-Tail, I snapped this screenshot of Boots standing between me and the camera. I just thought it looked kinda funny. Do you agree?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260630_HNI_0053.jpg" alt="Reese: Sure! You are more than welcome! What would you like to sell?" class="wp-image-18681" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2026/06/30/passing-around-skeletons/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-30T22:34:07-04:00"&gt;June 30, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-30T22:50:25-04:00"&gt;June 30, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260619_HNI_0017.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Chance to Back Out - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2026/06/28/chance-to-back-out/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2026/06/28/chance-to-back-out/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 02:54:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-6194" class="post-6194 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Chance to Back Out&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;On Wednesday, I received a goodbye letter from Wart Jr. in the mail. I&amp;#8217;m glad it was him, and not Lily, that moved out.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-wart-jr-out2026-sm.jpg" alt="Dear Jeff, Well, my streak continues... I just can't seem to settle down in any town for long. This is kind of odd, because I've said so many goodbyes, but this one actually hurts... Goodbye... Wart Jr." class="wp-image-6195" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;When I spoke with Candi, she offered to buy the trilobite I had in my pockets for 2,290 bells. I agreed to the trade, but then something unusual happened. She said she hoped I wasn&amp;#8217;t agreeing just to be nice&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-candi-agreeing-sm.jpg" alt="Candi: Oh? Really? Are you sure? I hope you're not agreeing just to be nice." class="wp-image-6196" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&amp;#8230;and she gave me a chance to back out of the deal! But I still sold it to her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-candi-rare-sm.jpg" alt="Candi: I know it's pretty rare, and I don't want you to regret your decision later, sweetie." class="wp-image-6197" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Usually, villagers are at the opposite end of the spectrum on things like this. Occasionally, they will even steal things from you outright, without giving you a chance to decline! So seeing Candi giving me a second chance was really surprising! Thanks for being nice for a change, Candi!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Nearby, I found a new house. Murphy the bear cub is my newest villager!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-murphy2026-sm.jpg" alt="Murphy: Hey! Who are you? I certainly don't know you! Hmmm... Jeff??? Nice name, laddie." class="wp-image-6198" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Murphy lived in Forest back in 2012, but there&amp;#8217;s an interesting twist to that: I never actually saw him at the time, at least not his face! See, he moved in on &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2012/10/31/halloween-2012/"&gt;Halloween&lt;/a&gt; that year. So when I got over to his house, he was already dressed up as Jack, demanding candy from me! And by the next time I played, he had already moved out! But at any rate, welcome (back) to Forest, Murphy!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Baabara was telling me about what she saw while walking by the beach one night. She said that she saw a body lying there in the sand!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-baabara-body-sm.jpg" alt="Baabara: But the other night, I saw something horrible!! There was this body, lying motionless on the sand!" class="wp-image-6199" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;And when she went back to see it a 2nd time, it was gone! Even though it sounded like she was talking about Gulliver, she seemed to think it was a ghost.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-baabara-ghost-sm.jpg" alt="Baabara: That was frightfully scary, right? I'm CERTAIN it was a ghost... I just know it! I'm fluffy!!" class="wp-image-6200" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;On Thursday, it was raining in town. Fortunately, Puck devised a plan to make the rain stop: Just simply wait for the rainy season to end. Genius.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-puck-rainy-sm.jpg" alt="Puck: The question is...how do we stop all this rain...? I know! All we have to do is wait for the rainy season to end!" class="wp-image-6202" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Meanwhile, Murphy did not seem very happy to see me. For no apparent reason. He&amp;#8217;s not making a very good impression on me so far.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-murphy-what-sm.jpg" alt="Murphy: What IS IT? Eh, it's you." class="wp-image-6203" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Anything that &lt;em&gt;can &lt;/em&gt;go wrong in this friendship, &lt;em&gt;will &lt;/em&gt;go wrong.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Hank told me that he thought he could show off for the ladies by bowling in the rain. I guess as long as he watches out for strikes&amp;#8230;of lightning.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-hank-bowling-sm.jpg" alt="Hank: Do you think watching me showing off with a little bowling in the rain would make the ladies swoon?" class="wp-image-6204" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I guess rain bowling is right up his alley. 🎳&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I played again tonight, and it was raining once again. Tom warned me not to spin my umbrella anywhere near him, because he didn&amp;#8217;t want to get wet.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-tom-spinning-sm.jpg" alt="Tom: Listen, pal...let's be clear in advance. Don't go spinning any umbrellas anywhere near me! I don't like getting wet." class="wp-image-6205" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You&amp;#8217;re lucky I like you. 😛&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I wasn&amp;#8217;t looking to start any beef with Tom, so I didn&amp;#8217;t get my umbrella out and spin it on him out of spite. Not this time, at least. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After making my rounds, I did a little ocean fishing (just 5-10 minutes) in hopes of snagging a coelacanth. I didn&amp;#8217;t find one, but I did catch a couple of barred knifejaws and several red snappers as well. But there will be plenty of time for good ocean fishing in September.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2026/06/28/chance-to-back-out/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-28T22:54:34-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-28T22:54:35-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ac-wart-jr-out2026-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>He Forgot the Words! - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2026/06/27/forgot-the-words/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2026/06/27/forgot-the-words/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 03:38:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-9577" class="post-9577 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;He Forgot the Words!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Last Saturday, Pascal popped up after I caught a scallop. And you know how he normally shares some words of wisdom? Well, he apparently forgot them this time! Oops!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pascal-forgot-sm.jpg" alt="Pascal: Oh maaan...I forgot what I was gonna say. Or, like, maybe my words just had somewhere else to be." class="wp-image-9578" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;But he still gave me a mermaid fishy dress and a pearl for the scallop.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;My former villager Tybalt returned as a tourist on Tuesday. It wasn&amp;#8217;t his first time visiting, but I was surprised when he said he was voted &amp;#8220;Buffest Forest Hero&amp;#8221; twice running. 😆 I think Louie might object to that statement! But it was good to see Tybalt again!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/tybalt-buffest-sm.jpg" alt="Tybalt: Remember me? I was voted Buffest Forest Hero twice running. I'm Tybalt!" class="wp-image-9579" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;June recently asked me for a new catchphrase to replace &amp;#8220;in spring.&amp;#8221; So I told her to say &amp;#8220;all summer&amp;#8221; now instead. I&amp;#8217;m keeping it seasonal, except for the fact that her &lt;em&gt;greeting &lt;/em&gt;is still about hibernation. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/june-summer-sm.jpg" alt="June: Time to hibernate! Stay awhile, all summer." class="wp-image-9580" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;On Wednesday, I found Gonzo camping at the campsite. He seemed nice, but I&amp;#8217;m not a big fan of koalas in Animal Crossing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/gonzo-camper-sm.jpg" alt="Gonzo, at the campsite: Heya! I'm just here to do some campin' for a spell. This sure is a nice island." class="wp-image-9581" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;On Thursday, Bones asked me to play a treasure hunt game with him. He only gave me three minutes instead of six, but that wasn&amp;#8217;t a problem&amp;#8230;because it took me just 17 seconds to find the buried treasure!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/treasure-62526-sm.jpg" alt="2:43 remains on the timer as I found the treasure." class="wp-image-9582" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The treasure was a vampire costume. What a fang-tastic reward. (Sorry for the bad pun. But it is a bloody good prize.) 🧛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The June Bug-Off was held today, but I played about an hour too late to participate. But that didn&amp;#8217;t stop Flick from asking me how I enjoyed the event! You&amp;#8217;d think he would&amp;#8217;ve noticed if I had participated or not, but I guess he was just obsessing over the bugs instead.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/flick-62726-sm.jpg" alt="Flick: How did you enjoy this Bug-Off, our regular celebration of bugs? Were you spiritually enriched?" class="wp-image-9583" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about the past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Last Saturday, K.K. performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Song&amp;#8221; for me, Bob, and Savannah.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;C.J. was in town on Monday, and I sold him 12 fish for 198,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I sold 32 bugs to Flick for 220,500 bells. That bumped my savings account balance up to 140 million bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Due to the Bug-Off today, there was no K.K. concert tonight.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The full slate of summer bugs and fish arrives next week! Hope to see you then!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2026/06/27/forgot-the-words/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-27T23:38:09-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-27T23:46:45-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pascal-forgot-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>So Long, Cat! - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2026/06/27/so-long-cat/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2026/06/27/so-long-cat/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 02:21:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-14059" class="post-14059 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;So Long, Cat!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;When I started up the game today, I received a letter from Big Top, thanking me for the medicine I gave him last week. He sent me a red drum.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I was glad that the letter from Big Top wasn&amp;#8217;t a goodbye letter. But I soon found out that another one of my favorites actually was leaving town: Rosie! 🙁&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8589-sm.jpg" alt="Rosie: Oh, J-love! I'm glad you stopped by...'cause I'm totally MOVING! So long, cat!" class="wp-image-14060" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I hate to see her go. She has lived here for just over a year, but it seems shorter than that. So long, Rosie! I hope we meet again!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Big Top&amp;#8217;s sickness has now moved on to Willow. I gave her some medicine too.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8590-sm.jpg" alt="Willow: I feel chills, my throat hurts, my nose is stuffed up... I'm normally SO sweet, but now I'm a mess." class="wp-image-14061" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Aww. Get wool soon!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was raining in town tonight, and I caught a couple of rainbow stags. I can&amp;#8217;t wait for the peak bug-hunting season that starts next Wednesday, so I can catch &lt;em&gt;all &lt;/em&gt;the good summer bugs! Woo!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8591-sm.jpg" alt="I caught a rainbow stag! Someone tell me, already! Where's the rainbow?!" class="wp-image-14062" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;As for my villagers, they had a wide variety of opinions about the rain today. Cube loved having fun splashing around it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8593-sm.jpg" alt="Cube: Splashing around in the rain is pretty fun, huh!" class="wp-image-14063" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;While Sydney has just had enough of the rain already.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8592-sm.jpg" alt="Sydney: On GameCube, Super J! You know, I've had enough of this rain. I hope it's sunny tomorrow." class="wp-image-14064" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Once 8:00 rolled around, I went over to the Roost to check out K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. I asked for a random song and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Etude&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8594-sm.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Etude." class="wp-image-14065" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After the show, I ran into Big Top just outside the museum. He said it would be nice for him to have a memento of me. So he asked if he could have my rainbow stag! I didn&amp;#8217;t want to give it away for free, but I asked if he&amp;#8217;d like to buy it instead. And he really came through: He offered me 14,038 bells for it! You got a deal! &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8595-sm.jpg" alt="Big Top: Hm... OK, will 14,038 bells do, in a coma? &amp;gt;That works!" class="wp-image-14066" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Assuming tonight was my last time playing for the month, I&amp;#8217;m ending June with 77,350,000 bells in savings. I haven&amp;#8217;t yet set my summer bug-hunting goals for this year, but I&amp;#8217;ll be sure to decide on that next week. I&amp;#8217;ve also (finally) cleaned up my leftover candy on the ground from Bunny Day. So my town is all ready to start bug hunting!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;See you next week! 🪲&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2026/06/27/so-long-cat/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-27T22:21:25-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-27T22:22:14-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RUU_8589-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Chief&amp;#039;s Pic - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/25/chiefs-pic/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/25/chiefs-pic/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 02:42:33 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8874" class="post-8874 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Chief&amp;#8217;s Pic&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yesterday, Chief was talking about the size of my house. He said it&amp;#8217;s so large that he&amp;#8217;s already planning on having a karaoke night at my house. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-karaoke.jpg" alt="Chief: All right! The next karaoke night is at your place! I'll post up some flyers!" class="wp-image-8875" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Pippy told me she had a makeover, and she asked me to guess what looked different. I think I normally choose &amp;#8220;haircut&amp;#8221; for this question, so I decided to instead suggest that maybe she lost weight. She said I was right, since she&amp;#8217;s been on a &amp;#8220;low taste&amp;#8221; diet. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pippy-taste.jpg" alt="Pippy: Huh?! I look skinnier?! I have been on a low-taste diet!" class="wp-image-8876" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pippy-paying.jpg" alt="Pippy: Maybe it's finally paying off, in a pond!" class="wp-image-8877" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Over by the museum, I listened in on an interesting conversation between Maple and Whitney. Maple asked Whitney what phrase describes her best&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/maple-phrase.jpg" alt="Maple: Hey, Whitney, what one phrase describes you best, and why, honey?" class="wp-image-8878" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Whitney replied with &amp;#8220;Every rose has a thorn,&amp;#8221; saying it was perfect for her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/whitney-rose.jpg" alt="Whitney: Ah! I've got it! Every rose has a thorn. That's perfect for me." class="wp-image-8879" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She continued, saying she&amp;#8217;s beautiful&amp;#8230;but also deadly.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/whitney-deadly.jpg" alt="Whitney: After all, I'm beautiful, but I am also...deadly." class="wp-image-8880" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;So of course, Maple pointed out that despite their thorns, roses aren&amp;#8217;t actually deadly. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/maple-deadly.jpg" alt="Maple: That's great, but... Um. Roses aren't deadly." class="wp-image-8881" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Whitney then followed up with &amp;#8220;not even&amp;#8230; POISON ROSES?&amp;#8221; I love these crazy conversations in the older games. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Today, Frobert was talking about muscles (as he often does, as a jock). After apparently answering his question wrong, he told me to do soccer until I can barely move, and then come talk to him. 🤷&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/frobert-soccer.jpg" alt="Frobert: Try doing soccer until you can barely move, then come talk to me!" class="wp-image-8882" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;But how will I get here?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Over by the river, Chief really surprised me&amp;#8230;by giving me his picture! Wow, thank you Chief!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-give.jpg" alt="Chief: Here... This is, uh, my picture, on a pig. Here's hoping you like it." class="wp-image-8883" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What are you doing to Truffles?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After selling some stuff at the shop, I took Chief&amp;#8217;s photo home and put it on display. I had to remove Eloise&amp;#8217;s pic to make room for it, though. Chief&amp;#8217;s favorite quote on the back is &amp;#8220;Harrumph.&amp;#8221; Sounds about right for him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-pic.jpg" alt="Chief's pic on display in house, next to Marina's pic. My Gulliver items are visible in the background." class="wp-image-8884" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Thanks again, Chief! See you all next week!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff365ea4b4ae589e18c26b092fe26946a6e14116b63065f41029c8c6138c7c8?s=98&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/25/chiefs-pic/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-25T22:42:33-04:00"&gt;June 25, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-25T22:45:37-04:00"&gt;June 25, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-karaoke.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Hopelessly Chasing - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/20/hopelessly-chasing/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/20/hopelessly-chasing/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8862" class="post-8862 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Hopelessly Chasing&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;On Thursday, Chief was talking about the upcoming Bug-Off. He said he&amp;#8217;s going to love watching me hopelessly chase after bugs! It sounds like he doesn&amp;#8217;t have much faith in me. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-hopeless.jpg" alt="Chief: I'm gonna love watching you hopelessly chasing after nasty critters!" class="wp-image-8863" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;But I probably won&amp;#8217;t be playing on Sunday for the event anyway, so I guess I can&amp;#8217;t prove him wrong this time. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Saharah was in town, asking me to help make deliveries for her. But she was really up in my face!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/saharah-right-away.jpg" alt="Saharah: Yes, yes, very important. This must be delivered right away." class="wp-image-8864" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;I took some carpeting over to Pelly (for Phyllis) and some wallpaper to Mabel at Able Sisters. And unlike last time, I actually remembered to return to Saharah to collect my reward. 😆 She gave me a meadow vista.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Pippy asked if I liked her clothes, and I must&amp;#8217;ve picked the sweet spot on the slider. She was thrilled that I liked her style, even though she kind of insulted the rest of the town in the process.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pippy-style.jpg" alt="Pippy: Really?! I knew you'd like my style, in a pond!" class="wp-image-8871" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/pippy-backwater.jpg" alt="Pippy: You and me are soooo the 'it' personalities in this backwater town!" class="wp-image-8865" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Marina was still sick with a cold, so I gave her some more medicine. But by yesterday, she was finally feeling better. She thanked me for the medicine and she gave me a Persian rug.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/marina-care.jpg" alt="Marina: Seriously, without your care, I'd probably still be sniffling in bed." class="wp-image-8867" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was raining in town yesterday, and Derwin said it was a great day for staying home and sleeping. Except that he was outside instead, getting rained on. (And not sleeping.) &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/derwin-rain.jpg" alt="Derwin: Days like today are great for staying at home and sleeping all day." class="wp-image-8866" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;But he has been annoying me lately. All he ever wants to do is have a competition to see who can catch a rarer bug. That&amp;#8217;s all he ever says any more, and I&amp;#8217;m not interested.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Tonight, I went over to the Roost for K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. He performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Gumbo&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/kk-62026.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Gumbo!" class="wp-image-8868" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After the show, Chief had a pop quiz for me. He said if I answered correctly, he&amp;#8217;d give me something &amp;#8220;unbelievably good.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/chief-good.jpg" alt="Chief: If you're right, I'll give you something unbelievably good, on a pig." class="wp-image-8869" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;So he asked me how he was feeling, and I guessed that he was feeling &amp;#8220;fine.&amp;#8221; That was correct, and he gave me a lab wall. I don&amp;#8217;t see how that&amp;#8217;s an &amp;#8220;unbelievably good&amp;#8221; item, but I guess I&amp;#8217;ll take it.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff365ea4b4ae589e18c26b092fe26946a6e14116b63065f41029c8c6138c7c8?s=98&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2026/06/20/hopelessly-chasing/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2026-06-20T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;June 20, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2026-06-21T05:43:42-04:00"&gt;June 21, 2026&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
